 on research issues representing his central concerns. The broad range of subjects is an apt reflection of Gottfried Kolde's own catholic research interests and his seminal work on noun determination and sociolinguistics. The contributions are in English, French, German and Italian, thus mirroring Kolde's refusal to limit himself to questions posed by German Studies alone and his interest in the phenomenon of languages in contact.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aDeutsch. 4aSchweiz. 4aSprachkontakt. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAbraham, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdamzik, Kirsten, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlumenthal, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöschenstein, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöschenstein, Renate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristen, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristen, Helen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDiehl, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDittmann, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhrich-Haefeli, Verena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeith, Karl-Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaas, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaegeman, Liliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangner, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenschen, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://i